and I'd like her to sing it.

00:37:38.356 --> 00:37:40.305
I think it's pretty fucking good.

00:37:47.385 --> 00:37:49.252
- How are you?
- I'm good. Hi!

00:37:49.283 --> 00:37:50.440
- It's so good to see you.
- How are you?

00:37:50.472 --> 00:37:52.390
- You were so good.
- The trip was fine?

00:37:52.422 --> 00:37:54.339
- Yeah.
- Phil didn't bother you?

00:37:54.371 --> 00:37:55.476
Gail was so nice.

00:37:56.258 --> 00:37:58.375
So, listen, we're gonna
sing that song, all right?

00:37:58.406 --> 00:38:00.397
I did an arrangement -
kind of not so great -

00:38:00.429 --> 00:38:02.285
- but stick with it.
- No, I can't.

00:38:02.316 --> 00:38:03.463
- I'm sorry.
- Yeah, you're coming.

00:38:03.494 --> 00:38:06.435
Please. It's not funny.
Jack, don't fuck around.

00:38:07.467 --> 00:38:09.500
All you gotta do is trust me.

00:38:10.376 --> 00:38:12.304
That's all you gotta do.

00:38:14.410 --> 00:38:16.423
I'm gonna sing it either way, so...

00:38:27.507 --> 00:38:31.344
- Steve...
- "Trust me." OK.

00:38:32.323 --> 00:38:34.388
- You have to go sing.
- I'm not going out there, no.

00:42:04.577 --> 00:42:07.528
- Oh, my God! There's so many people.
- Pretty fucking good, man.

00:42:07.559 --> 00:42:08.602
Pretty fucking good.

00:42:08.633 --> 00:42:10.531
The way the guitar started...

00:42:10.562 --> 00:42:13.545
I thought maybe I set it in the wrong key,
and the tempo was too fast.

00:42:13.576 --> 00:42:15.713
