01:45:57.938 --> 01:46:00.856
I wouldn't say I was hiding it.
I just um...

01:46:03.745 --> 01:46:06.737
I started puttin' it down to paper
when we were at home.

01:46:08.906 --> 01:46:12.785
I don't know, it sort of fell out of me,
I guess, and onto this page.

01:46:16.883 --> 01:46:18.937
And I put it in here, and I thought...

01:46:21.897 --> 01:46:24.963
I thought maybe you'd find it when...

01:46:28.852 --> 01:46:30.854
..when you came back to you, maybe.

01:46:39.967 --> 01:46:41.843
Well, I found it.

01:46:49.893 --> 01:46:51.832
Listen. Um...

01:46:56.858 --> 01:46:57.953
Um...

01:47:12.967 --> 01:47:14.959
I'm sorry.

01:47:21.881 --> 01:47:23.007
It's OK.

01:47:29.837 --> 01:47:31.933
It's OK. It's not your fault.

01:47:31.964 --> 01:47:33.956
I'm sorry I did that.

01:47:35.999 --> 01:47:37.949
It's OK.

01:47:37.981 --> 01:47:40.816
It's not your fault. It's a disease.

01:47:42.880 --> 01:47:44.882
No, but I embarrassed you.

01:47:46.926 --> 01:47:49.940
- I embarrassed you, and I...
- I'm not embarrassed of you.

01:47:50.847 --> 01:47:52.035
It was so wrong.

01:47:53.026 --> 01:47:55.966
And then your...then your dad...

01:47:58.864 --> 01:48:00.835
My father loves you. It's OK.

01:48:03.004 --> 01:48:04.933
I know, but I...

01:48:07.060 --> 01:48:09.875
- It's OK.
- I know, but I...

01:48:10.011 --> 01:48:11.971
It's OK.

01:48:13.024 --> 01:48:14.901
It's OK.

01:48:15.975 --> 01:48:19.853
I have figured out what I think is
the best solution for both of us.

01:48:19.884 --> 01:48:21.928
Jack should come out on tour with me.

01:48:21.959 --> 01:48:24.076
We'll start with our duets.
I know he's gonna be able

01:48:24.858 --> 01:48:27.047
- to play by himself.
- You realise that's not an option.

01:48:27.079 --> 01:48:30.906
He's... He's so inside of his art
in a way he has never been.

01:48:30.937 --> 01:48:33.095
- He can hear himself again.
- Ally, there is no way

01:48:33.877 --> 01:48:36.912
that you can take Jack on tour with you.
There's no way.

01:48:50.038 --> 01:48:51.978
Do you understand what I'm saying?

01:48:52.009 --> 01:48:55.043
If you can't make that happen,
then fucking cancel the tour.

01:48:55.074 --> 01:48:57.076
I don't know what to tell you.

01:49:14.134 --> 01:49:18.003
I think if we had a better band name,
we might've made it.

01:49:20.994 --> 01:49:24.101
Or maybe it was cos we looked like
a father and son duo.

01:49:24.133 --> 01:49:28.074
Not many of those around.

01:49:28.105 --> 01:49:31.932
I was not a good look for you,
that's for sure.

01:49:31.964 --> 01:49:34.164
Not my fault I couldn't find
a better guitar player

01:49:34.946 --> 01:49:37.000
in the whole goddamn state.

01:49:43.036 --> 01:49:44.163
Where in the fuck is it?

01:49:45.153 --> 01:49:47.030
Right here.

01:49:55.027 --> 01:49:56.153
Thanks for the ride.

01:50:00.001 --> 01:50:01.169
Sure thing, Jack.

01:50:03.171 --> 01:50:07.049
Hey, you know...when I...

01:50:15.130 --> 01:50:17.987
..when I said I...
you know, when I...

01:50:25.076 --> 01:50:27.109
..took your voice, you know.

01:50:36.994 --> 01:50:39.028
It was you I idolised. It wasn't Dad.

01:51:27.073 --> 01:51:28.219
Come here.

01:51:30.190 --> 01:51:32.265
What was that, guy?

01:51:42.254 --> 01:51:44.099
Hey.

01:51:44.267 --> 01:51:46.164
Hey.

01:51:48.051 --> 01:51:50.053
I wanna know how you hear this.

01:51:51.137 --> 01:51:53.212
That sounded unbelievable,
what you were playing.

01:51:53.243 --> 01:51:55.214
- Thank you.
- It's nice to hear it.

01:51:55.245 --> 01:51:59.218
Thank you, and I had
the beautiful backdrop of you and Charlie.

01:52:01.189 --> 01:52:03.274
I only heard it in my mind
for so many weeks,

01:52:03.306 --> 01:52:06.266
so it's good to hear it... You know.

01:52:06.297 --> 01:52:10.124
- The words are beautiful.
- ..in the real thing. In the real thing.

01:52:15.233 --> 01:52:17.277
- Well, you want me to do that?
- Mm-hm.

01:52:17.308 --> 01:52:20.217
Oh, God, I don't know.
I knew you were gonna ask me.

01:52:46.158 --> 01:52:48.181
Back from the dead.

01:52:50.162 --> 01:52:52.237
- Hey, sorry. Were you waiting long?
- No, no.

01:52:54.156 --> 01:52:56.168
Uh... Ally's not home.

01:52:56.199 --> 01:52:58.274
No, I told her I'd meet her here,
if that's OK.

01:52:58.305 --> 01:53:00.120
Of course, yeah.

01:53:05.333 --> 01:53:07.147
Here you go.

01:53:07.178 --> 01:53:10.275
Hey, thanks for taking care of my girl
when I was gone.

01:53:10.306 --> 01:53:12.183
Anything for her.

01:53:13.236 --> 01:53:15.374
She told me about that European leg.

01:53:16.302 --> 01:53:19.357
That's a hell of an accomplishment
this soon out of the gate.

01:53:20.139 --> 01:53:25.268
Shit, I remember it was like...ten years
before I even went across the pond.

01:53:25.300 --> 01:53:27.249
It was summer, 2004.

01:53:27.280 --> 01:53:29.262
Shit, was it?

01:53:35.184 --> 01:53:37.165
We're not exactly friends here.

01:53:40.189 --> 01:53:43.203
While you've been away,
we've been back here in serious triage,

01:53:43.234 --> 01:53:45.330
trying to clean up your fucking mess.

01:53:45.361 --> 01:53:47.372
Barely finding our way through it.

01:53:49.353 --> 01:53:53.399
You almost single-handedly derailed
her whole career. You understand that?

01:53:54.181 --> 01:53:56.183
She's never gonna say this to you.

01:53:57.226 --> 01:53:58.394
She loves you too much.

01:54:00.364 --> 01:54:03.232
Just by staying married to you,
she looks like a joke.

01:54:03.263 --> 01:54:04.410
It's embarrassing.

01:54:06.265 --> 01:54:08.403
Let's be honest, we both know
it's only a matter of time

01:54:09.185 --> 01:54:11.374
before that's pushed aside again
for the real thing.

01:54:12.386 --> 01:54:14.325
And when that happens...

01:54:15.410 --> 01:54:18.194
..I don't want her anywhere near you.

01:54:29.505 --> 01:54:30.632
Hey.

01:54:34.531 --> 01:54:35.678
I have some good news.

01:54:36.637 --> 01:54:38.556
- Yeah?
- Mm-hm.

01:54:38.587 --> 01:54:40.558
I'm not gonna go to Europe.

01:54:41.538 --> 01:54:45.626
We're gonna cancel the rest of the tour,
and I'm just gonna be here all summer.

01:54:48.514 --> 01:54:49.671
Isn't that great?

01:54:51.599 --> 01:54:53.726
- What happened?
- Nothing happened.

01:54:54.675 --> 01:54:57.730
The label just loves the record,
and it's doing so well

01:54:57.762 --> 01:55:02.735
and they wanna keep with the momentum
and have me make another one.

01:55:03.768 --> 01:55:07.553
Rez is super psyched, so it'll be great.

01:55:09.721 --> 01:55:11.765
So tonight's gonna be my last show.

01:55:13.683 --> 01:55:16.582
Going out with a bang at the Forum.

01:55:19.595 --> 01:55:20.617
Great.

01:55:20.648 --> 01:55:21.743
Yeah.

01:55:25.705 --> 01:55:27.697
Why don't you come with me?

01:55:29.688 --> 01:55:33.639
We can sing Shallow together.
The fans will go crazy to see you.

01:55:37.560 --> 01:55:38.801
Come on, cowboy.

01:55:43.722 --> 01:55:45.662
Yeah, why not? OK.

01:55:47.601 --> 01:55:48.706
Yeah?

01:55:48.738 --> 01:55:50.594
OK, good.

01:55:50.625 --> 01:55:51.803
I'll have a car come get you.

01:55:52.584 --> 01:55:54.576
When I... Once I get there.

01:55:54.607 --> 01:55:55.744
I'll go meet you there.

01:56:04.805 --> 01:56:06.807
I'll see you soon, OK?

01:56:11.676 --> 01:56:13.594
Hey.

01:56:13.698 --> 01:56:15.679
What?

01:56:17.671 --> 01:56:19.787
I just wanted to take
another look at you.

01:56:23.729 --> 01:56:25.783
Bye, honey.

01:56:26.826 --> 01:56:28.828
Bye.

01:56:59.669 --> 01:57:00.826
Come here, Charlie.

01:57:00.858 --> 01:57:02.745
Come here.

01:57:38.748 --> 01:57:40.864
Thank you so much
for bringing us all here together.

01:57:40.896 --> 01:57:44.743
Please look over
all of the dancers tonight and the band.

01:57:44.775 --> 01:57:45.849
And my husband, Jackson.

01:57:45.880 --> 01:57:48.800
We're so excited for him
to be here with us.

01:57:48.831 --> 01:57:50.718
We got a big night.

01:57:50.749 --> 01:57:51.907
We're at the Forum, LA.
Let's do this.

02:00:00.997 --> 02:00:03.844
- Is he here?
- He's not here.

02:00:03.875 --> 02:00:06.899
- He's not here?
- We have to do Shallow regardless, OK?

02:00:06.931 --> 02:00:09.902
The guitar's up there.
Everything's gonna remain the same.

02:00:09.934 --> 02:00:11.039
- What?
- The guitar's up there.

02:00:11.821 --> 02:00:13.927
Everything's gonna remain the same.
Both verses.

02:00:13.958 --> 02:00:17.045
- I'm sure it was just a bit much for him.
- Please send somebody to the house.

02:00:17.826 --> 02:00:19.995
- I'm doing it right now.
- I have 15 seconds.

02:00:50.044 --> 02:00:52.860
Give it up for my husband, Jackson!

02:01:52.010 --> 02:01:53.980
I can stay, if you want.

02:02:18.044 --> 02:02:19.087
Aargh!

02:02:31.193 --> 02:02:35.967
Some kid started singing one of his songs
in a bar I was in the other night.

02:02:39.054 --> 02:02:41.108
They're playing his songs everywhere.

02:02:45.133 --> 02:02:47.124
At first I got angry.

02:02:49.012 --> 02:02:51.107
I don't know why.

02:02:52.067 --> 02:02:54.027
I guess I felt like...

02:02:55.195 --> 02:02:58.166
.."How can any of these people
feel like they knew him?"

02:02:59.083 --> 02:03:01.033
Who he really was.

02:03:04.140 --> 02:03:06.163
But then something changed.

02:03:08.123 --> 02:03:10.125
And it soothed me.

02:03:13.045 --> 02:03:17.027
That it wasn't...
wasn't all for fucking nothing.

02:03:18.018 --> 02:03:20.208
The last thing I did was lie to him.

02:03:23.023 --> 02:03:24.170
Listen to me.

02:03:26.192 --> 02:03:28.132
It isn't your fault.

02:03:30.051 --> 02:03:31.177
It just isn't.

02:03:33.199 --> 02:03:36.036
You know whose fault it was?

02:03:36.067 --> 02:03:37.110
Jack.

02:03:40.049 --> 02:03:41.154
That's it.

02:03:43.063 --> 02:03:44.230
No-one else.

02:03:44.262 --> 02:03:47.067
Not you, not me.

02:03:47.265 --> 02:03:49.079
No-one but Jack.

02:03:49.110 --> 02:03:51.029
I just keep...

02:03:52.051 --> 02:03:55.148
..going over and over it,
over it in my head.

02:03:59.119 --> 02:04:03.259
Jack talked about how music is
essentially 12 notes between any octave.

02:04:07.169 --> 02:04:09.286
12 notes and the octave repeats.

02:04:13.154 --> 02:04:15.125
It's the same story.

02:04:16.168 --> 02:04:18.295
Told over and over.

02:04:19.233 --> 02:04:21.088
Forever.

02:04:22.277 --> 02:04:25.259
All any artist can offer the world...

02:04:25.290 --> 02:04:28.116
is how they see those 12 notes.

02:04:28.147 --> 02:04:30.108
That's it.

02:04:30.295 --> 02:04:32.255
Hm.

02:04:37.146 --> 02:04:39.157
<i>He loved how you see them.</i>

02:04:41.128 --> 02:04:43.120
<i>He just kept saying...</i>

02:04:43.318 --> 02:04:47.113
<i>.."I love how she sees them, Bobby."</i>

02:04:55.225 --> 02:04:58.092
Hello, I'm Ally Maine.

02:05:00.198 --> 02:05:03.326
Thank you for being here tonight
to honour my husband.

02:05:04.108 --> 02:05:05.255
He wrote a song for me.

02:05:06.162 --> 02:05:08.300
I'd like to sing it for him tonight.

02:05:10.229 --> 02:05:12.304
And, with your help, maybe I can.

02:05:14.150 --> 02:05:16.162
Thank you.

02:05:17.132 --> 02:05:18.185
Really.

02:05:19.196 --> 02:05:21.135
Thank you.

